<p>Chronic infantile neurologic cutaneous and articular (CINCA) syndrome is a severe chronic inflammatory disease of early onset, characterized by cutaneous symptoms, central nervous system involvement, and arthropathy (Feldmann et al., 2002).</p>

<p>[Feldmann, J., Prieur, A.-M., Quartier, P., Berquin, P., Certain, S., Cortis, E., Teillac-Hamel, D., Fischer, A., de Saint Basile, G. Chronic infantile neurological cutaneous and articular syndrome is caused by mutations in CIAS1, a gene highly expressed in polymorphonuclear cells and chondrocytes. Am. J. Hum. Genet. 71: 198-203, 2002. Note: Erratum: Am. J. Hum. Genet. 71: 1258 only, 2002.]<br/></p>